<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[189,259,366,392]" box="[189,259,366,392]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,259,366,392]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,259,366,392]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Notes</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[189,1399,412,545]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
In a similar circumstance to that described under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Betrem" authorityYear="1967" box="[792,945,412,438]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Phalerimeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[792,945,412,438]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Phalerimeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
above, 
<bibRefCitation author="Argaman Q." box="[1042,1239,412,439]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="171 - 222" refId="ref31690" refString="Argaman Q. 1996. Generic synopsis of Scoliidae (Hymenoptera, Scolioidea). Annales Historico- Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici 88: 171 - 222." type="journal article" year="1996">Argaman (1996)</bibRefCitation>
regarded the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Argaman" authorityYear="1996" box="[262,381,447,473]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Guigliana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[262,381,447,473]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Guigliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as having been established by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bradley J. C." box="[754,947,447,474]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="186 - 196" refId="ref32132" refString="Bradley J. C. 1964 a. The type-specimens of the Scoliidae described by Amedee Lepeletier, Comte de Saint-Fargeau (with notes by J. G. Betrem) and by the Marchese Massimiliano Spinola. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; Giacomo Doria &quot; 74: 186 - 196." type="journal article" year="1964">Bradley (1964a)</bibRefCitation>
despite appearing therein as a nomen nudum only. 
<bibRefCitation author="Argaman Q." box="[342,555,482,509]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="171 - 222" refId="ref31690" refString="Argaman Q. 1996. Generic synopsis of Scoliidae (Hymenoptera, Scolioidea). Annales Historico- Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici 88: 171 - 222." type="journal article" year="1996">Argaman’s (1996)</bibRefCitation>
usage can be taken as establishing a new available name, but by then it was long preoccupied by Betrem’s (in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bradley J. C. &amp; Betrem J. G." box="[642,926,518,545]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="287 - 327" refId="ref32226" refString="Bradley J. C. &amp; Betrem J. G. 1967. The types of the Scoliidae described by Frederick Smith (Hymenoptera) with descriptions of new taxa, and notes on the Oriental localities where Alfred Russel Wallace collected. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History). Entomology 20 (7): 287 - 327." type="journal article" year="1967">Bradley &amp; Betrem 1967</bibRefCitation>
) usage of it for a different taxon.
</paragraph>
